songs.title: Meet Me At Our Spot

description.plain:
Meet Me At Our Spot is the 8th song on The Anxiety ’s debut project titled The Anxiety. The verses on the song speak of a paralyzing anxiety that often leads to insomnia at night.

Both Tyler Cole and Willow express this anxiety in their individual verses.  They seem to experience it when they are in an isolated environment.

The chorus of the song eludes to a more lively and optimistic vibe that they both experience when they spend time together.

songs.title: Poolside

description.plain:
‘Poolside’ is the 4th song on THE ANXIETY album by The Anxiety. The theme of the song gives off a very chilled, poolside vibe with the beach references and a lively chorus.

If I had to describe this song using experiences, I would say: windows down, sun out and driving to the beach with our sunglasses on.

A deeper inspection of the lyrics reveals an annoyance, almost a frustration about how overall society turns a blind eye towards the real issues that plague our world.  Issues such as global warming and racism.
